Why is using NULL preferable here?  The standard paradigm as I understand
it is


         ylab = "", xlim, ylim, ...)
...
            if(missing(xlim)) {
                xlim <- range(x, na.rm = TRUE)
                xlim <- xlim + c(-1, 1) * (0.1 * diff(xlim))
            }

In S there is a problem with passing down missingness, but not in R.

Brian

